<emphasis id="22A0EA81FFBE061CFF5EAD14440AD564" bold="true" box="[199,328,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Puparium.</emphasis>
Formed within the mine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58CE6518FFBE061CFF5EAD7F411AD5F4" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="106B3693FFBE061CFF5EAD7F411AD5F4" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="22A0EA81FFBE061CFF5EAD7F440DD541" bold="true" box="[199,335,332,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Comments.</emphasis>
The leaf mine seems consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="D7D44D10FFBE061CFC8FAD7F46B3D541" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[790,1009,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="22A0EA81FFBE061CFC8FAD7F46B3D541" box="[790,1009,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Ophiomyia beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has been found at the same location and is recorded from 
<taxonomicName id="D7D44D10FFBE061CFE7EAD5C4734D5AC" box="[487,630,367,392]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hypochaeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22A0EA81FFBE061CFE7EAD5C4734D5AC" box="[487,630,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Hypochaeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="74454B62FFBE061CFC81AD5C46BCD5AC" author="Hering, E. M." box="[792,1022,367,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" refId="ref14381" refString="Hering, E. M. (1957) Bestimmungstabellen der Blattminen von Europa einschliesslich des Mittelmeerbeckens und der Kanarischen Inseln, vol. 1. Uitgeverij Dr. W. Junk, The Hague, 648 pp." type="book" year="1957">Hering 1957, p. 557</bibRefCitation>
). The reared adult is unfortunately in very poor condition, with the head and most legs missing, in addition to being a female. TSF has found similar midrib-based mines on 
<taxonomicName id="D7D44D10FFBE061CFE07AD8A4762D5F4" box="[414,544,439,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hypochaeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="radicata">
<emphasis id="22A0EA81FFBE061CFE07AD8A4762D5F4" box="[414,544,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">H. radicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. at both St. Andrews University and in Durham.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
